sx.blah.discord.handle.audio

Interface IAudioProvider

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IAudioProcessor
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AudioInputStreamProvider, AudioPlayer, AudioPlayer.Track, DefaultProcessor, DefaultProvider, FileProvider, GlobalProvider, MultiProcessor, PauseableProcessor, ProviderQueue, URLProvider, VolumeProcessor

    public interface IAudioProvider
    This represents a class which can provide audio to discord.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static class  IAudioProvider.AudioEncodingType
      The types of specific audio handling Discord4J supports.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      default IAudioProvider.AudioEncodingType getAudioEncodingType()
      This is called to determine the type of audio data provided by this provider.
      default int getChannels()
      Gets the number of channels in this audio.
      boolean isReady()
      This is called to determine whether the audio provider is ready to provide audio or not.
      byte[] provide()
      This is called to retrieve the actual audio data.

    • Method Detail

      • isReady

        boolean isReady()
        This is called to determine whether the audio provider is ready to provide audio or not. When it is not ready, no audio data queries will be attempted.
        Returns:
        True if ready, false if otherwise.

      • provide

        byte[] provide()
        This is called to retrieve the actual audio data. This should attempt to return 20 ms of data. The audio must also respect the encoding type returned by getAudioEncodingType().
        Returns:
        The audio data.

      • getChannels

        default int getChannels()
        Gets the number of channels in this audio. NOTE: This only matters if getAudioEncodingType() does not return IAudioProvider.AudioEncodingType.OPUS.
        Returns:
        The number of channels. It returns 2 (stereo) by default.

      • getAudioEncodingType

        default IAudioProvider.AudioEncodingType getAudioEncodingType()
        This is called to determine the type of audio data provided by this provider. This determines how the audio data is processed.
        Returns:
        The audio encoding type. By default this returns IAudioProvider.AudioEncodingType.PCM.
